OL,6,FThe Bank of England is set to
OL,7,Fincrease its base rate to 4.5 per
OL,8,Fcent today, the highest figure since
OL,9,Fthe 2008 financial crash.
OL,11,FIt marks the 12th consecutive time
OL,12,Fthe Bank has increased its base rate
OL,13,Fsince late 2021, as part of a bid to
OL,14,Fcurb soaring inflation.
OL,16,FThe Bank of England's base rate
OL,17,Fimpacts the vast majority of
OL,18,Fhouseholds in the UK, including those
OL,19,Fwith a mortgage, savings, debt and
OL,20,Fpensions.
